			<node ID="ID_1034095376" TEXT="Least laxity first (LLF) is a real-time scheduling algorithm for periodic tasks. Slack time or laxity is the amount of time between when a task would complete if it started now and its next deadline. This is the size of the available scheduling window. Laxity can be expressed as Laxity=(deadline time)&#8722;(current time)&#8722;(processor time needed)" />
